Juliana Taiwo-Obalonye, Abuja President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated former President, General Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida on his 78th birthday. According to a  statement by Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, Buhari in a message to the former Head of State, said: “On behalf of the Federal Executive Council, my family and all Nigerians, please accept my warm felicitations on your 78th birthday. “On this special day of your life, the reminiscences of your courage and invaluable service to the army in protecting the sovereignty of the country come to the fore. Thank you for the role of statesman you are playing in the affairs the nation. “As you age gracefully, the country will continue to look up to you for guidance and wisdom. May Allah continue to increase your health and grant you the strength to give your best to your family and the nation.”